productModelNumber.name: productModelNumber
productModelNumber.description: This string displays the units model number

productModelDescr.name: productModelDescr
productModelDescr.description: This string displays a brief description of the unit

productElementId.name: productElementId
productElementId.description: This string is the same information that is in the element id field located in the utilities Screen of the unit's user interface. This field can be set from either location.

productSoftwareRev.name: productSoftwareRev
productSoftwareRev.description: This string reports the units current software revision

productHardwareRev.name: productHardwareRev
productHardwareRev.description: This string reports the units hardware revision

productSerialNum.name: productSerialNum
productSerialNum.description: This string displays the unit's serial number

productPhysicalAddress.name: productPhysicalAddress
productPhysicalAddress.description: This string displays the unit's physical ethernet address

productNmsAddress.name: productNmsAddress
productNmsAddress.description: This string displays the unit's NMS address which is used to identify it to the TxPORT management products

productLabelTableEntry.name: productLabelTableEntry
productLabelTableEntry.description: An entry in the product label table.

labelTableValue.name: labelTableValue
labelTableValue.description: The data associated with the label.

mgmtPortsTableEntry.name: mgmtPortsTableEntry
mgmtPortsTableEntry.description: An entry in the Management Ports table.

mgmtPortsTableIndex.name: mgmtPortsTableIndex
mgmtPortsTableIndex.description: The index into the Management Ports table.

mgmtPortsDescription.name: mgmtPortsDescription
mgmtPortsDescription.description: Contains a textual description of the port.

mgmtPortsElementID.name: mgmtPortsElementID
mgmtPortsElementID.description: This object signifies the name of the device.

mgmtPortsMode.name: mgmtPortsMode
mgmtPortsMode.description: This object signifies the method used by the port to report alarms.

mgmtPortsDialPrefix.name: mgmtPortsDialPrefix
mgmtPortsDialPrefix.description: This object contains the dial string prefix for a modem connected to the port.

mgmtPortsPrimaryDialString.name: mgmtPortsPrimaryDialString
mgmtPortsPrimaryDialString.description: This object contains the primary dial string for a modem connected to the port.

mgmtPortsSecondaryDialString.name: mgmtPortsSecondaryDialString
mgmtPortsSecondaryDialString.description: This object contains the secondary dial string for a modem connected to the port.

mgmtPortsExtInitString.name: mgmtPortsExtInitString
mgmtPortsExtInitString.description: This object contains the init string for a modem connected to the port.

mgmtPortsCompressedSlip.name: mgmtPortsCompressedSlip
mgmtPortsCompressedSlip.description: This object specifies if SLIP compression is to be used.

mgmtPortsInternalModem.name: mgmtPortsInternalModem
mgmtPortsInternalModem.description: This object signifies if the internal modem (when present) is enabled.

dbuConfigTableEntry.name: dbuConfigTableEntry
dbuConfigTableEntry.description: An entry in the Dial Backup Configuration table.

dbuConfigTableIndex.name: dbuConfigTableIndex
dbuConfigTableIndex.description: The index into the Dial Backup table.

dbuDescription.name: dbuDescription
dbuDescription.description: Contains a textual description of the dbu.

dbuRate.name: dbuRate
dbuRate.description: This object is the identifier of the current DDS DBU rate. The values mean: dbuRate2400 the DBU interface is operating at 2400bps dbuRate4800 the DBU interface is operating at 4800bps dbuRate9600 the DBU interface is operating at 9600bps dbuRate19200 the DBU interface is operating at 19200bps dbuRate38400 the DBU interface is operating at 38400bps dbuRate56000 the DBU interface is operating at 56000bps dbuRate57600 the DBU interface is operating at 57600bps dbuRate64000 the DBU interface is operating at 64000bps

dbuMode.name: dbuMode
dbuMode.description: This object is the identifier of the current mode that the Dial Backup Unit is operating in. The values mean: dbuModeOrig The dial backup unit is operating in the originate mode dbuModeAnsw The dial backup unit is operating in the answer mode dbuModeNotAvail The dial backup unit's mode is not available dbuModeCallbackOrig The dial backup unit is operating in the callback originate mode dbuModeCallbackAnsw The dial backup unit is operating in the callback mode dbuModeMaster The dial backup unit is configured as a master unit dbuModeSlave The dial backup unit is configured as a slave unit

dbuFormat.name: dbuFormat
dbuFormat.description: This object is the identifier of the current format that the Dial Backup Unit is operating in. The values mean: dbuFormatSync The dial backup unit is operating in the synchronous format dbuFormatAsync The dial backup unit is operating in the asynchronous format dbuFormatNotAvail The dial backup unit's format is not available

dbuNumber.name: dbuNumber
dbuNumber.description: This string is the currently programmed number for the dial backup unit to call

dbuStatus.name: dbuStatus
dbuStatus.description: This object is the identifier of the current Dial Backup Unit operating status. The values mean: dbuStatusDisabled The dial backup unit is either not installed or disabled dbuStatusEnabled The dial backup unit is installed and enabled dbuStatusActive The dial backup unit is currently active dbuStatusLocked The dial backup unit is in a locked state dbuStatusConnecting The dial backup unit is in the process of connecting dbuStatusDisallowed The dial backup unit is currently not allowed to activate due to the Time Of Day Enable settings dbuStatusAwaitingCall The dial backup unit is in the process of waiting for an incoming call dbuStatusDialing The dial backup unit is in the process of placing a call dbuStatusDisconnecting The dial backup unit is in the process of disconnecting dbuStatusTesting The dial backup unit is in the process of testing dbuStatusTestPassed The dial backup unit has passed a self-test dbuStatusTestFailed The dial backup unit has failed a self-test

dbuCommand.name: dbuCommand
dbuCommand.description: This object is the identifier of the current setting that the Dial Backup Unit is operating in. The values mean: dbuCommandDisable The dial backup unit is not to operate dbuCommandEnable The dial backup unit is to operate, subject to Activator and line conditions only dbuCommandActivate The dial backup unit is to operate, irregardless of line conditions dbuCommandLock The dial backup unit is to continue operating, irregardless of line conditions dbuCommandEnableDaily The dial backup unit is to operate, subject to Activator, line conditions, and the Time Of Day Enable fields dbuCommandTest The dial backup unit is commanded to test the link.

dbuActivator1.name: dbuActivator1
dbuActivator1.description: This object is the identifier of the current trigger that will activate the Dial Backup Unit. The values mean: dbuActivatorLOS The dial backup unit is activated by a LOS alarm condition dbuActivatorOOS The dial backup unit is activated by an OOS alarm condition dbuActivatorOOF The dial backup unit is activated by an OOF alarm condition dbuActivatorAny The dial backup unit is activated by a LOS, OOS, or OOF alarm condition dbuActivatorES The dial backup unit is activated by an ES alarm condition dbuActivatorSES The dial backup unit is activated by an SES alarm condition dbuActivatorUAS The dial backup unit is activated by an UAS alarm condition dbuActivatorLOF The dial backup unit is activated by an LOF alarm condition dbuActivatorRAS The dial backup unit is activated by an RAS alarm condition dbuActivatorAIS The dial backup unit is activated by an AIS alarm condition dbuActivatorBPV The dial backup unit is activated by an BPV alarm condition

dbuActivator2.name: dbuActivator2
dbuActivator2.description: This object is the identifier of the current trigger that will activate the Dial Backup Unit. The values mean: dbuActivatorLOS The dial backup unit is activated by a LOS alarm condition dbuActivatorOOS The dial backup unit is activated by a OOS alarm condition dbuActivatorOOF The dial backup unit is activated by a OOF alarm condition dbuActivatorAny The dial backup unit is activated by a LOS, OOS, or OOF alarm condition dbuActivatorES The dial backup unit is activated by an ES alarm condition dbuActivatorSES The dial backup unit is activated by an SES alarm condition dbuActivatorUAS The dial backup unit is activated by an UAS alarm condition dbuActivatorLOF The dial backup unit is activated by an LOF alarm condition dbuActivatorRAS The dial backup unit is activated by an RAS alarm condition dbuActivatorAIS The dial backup unit is activated by an AIS alarm condition dbuActivatorBPV The dial backup unit is activated by an BPV alarm condition

dbuDialStr.name: dbuDialStr
dbuDialStr.description: This string is the dial string sent to the dial backup unit during every connection attempt

dbuInitStr.name: dbuInitStr
dbuInitStr.description: This string is the initialization string sent to the dial backup unit before every connection attempt

dbuHangupStr.name: dbuHangupStr
dbuHangupStr.description: This string is the hangup command string sent to the dial backup unit after every successful call

dbuPasswordStr.name: dbuPasswordStr
dbuPasswordStr.description: This string is the prompt character and password string for the dial backup unit in Callback DBU

dbuSecurity.name: dbuSecurity
dbuSecurity.description: Enables security on dial backup unit.

dbuDtrDial.name: dbuDtrDial
dbuDtrDial.description: Enables DTR dial feature on dial backup unit.

dbuISDNSwitchType.name: dbuISDNSwitchType
dbuISDNSwitchType.description: Specifies the switch type for the ISDN DBU.

dbuISDNSwitchVersion.name: dbuISDNSwitchVersion
dbuISDNSwitchVersion.description: Specifies the switch version for the ISDN DBU.

dbuISDNSPID.name: dbuISDNSPID
dbuISDNSPID.description: Specifies the SPID for the ISDN DBU.

dbuISDNDDNUM.name: dbuISDNDDNUM
dbuISDNDDNUM.description: Specifies the Data Directory Number for the ISDN DBU.

dbuResetStringsTable.name: dbuResetStringsTable
dbuResetStringsTable.description: A table of COLD START reprogramming strings for the dial backup unit.

dbuResetConfigEntryIndex.name: dbuResetConfigEntryIndex
dbuResetConfigEntryIndex.description: The index into the Dial Backup table.

dbuResetString.name: dbuResetString
dbuResetString.description: This string is one of the dial backup unit's COLD START reprogramming strings

dbuStartStopTableEntry.name: dbuStartStopTableEntry
dbuStartStopTableEntry.description: An entry in the Dial Backup Start Stop table.

dbuStartStopConfigEntryIndex.name: dbuStartStopConfigEntryIndex
dbuStartStopConfigEntryIndex.description: The index into the Dial Backup table.

dbuStartStopDayOfWeek.name: dbuStartStopDayOfWeek
dbuStartStopDayOfWeek.description: The index into the Dial Backup Start Stop times table.

dbuStart.name: dbuStart
dbuStart.description: This object is the beginning of an allowable window for Dial Backup Activation.

dbuStop.name: dbuStop
dbuStop.description: This object is the end of an allowable window for Dial Backup Activation.

t1e1ConfigTable.name: t1e1ConfigTable
t1e1ConfigTable.description: The T1 and E1 Configuration Table.

t1e1ConfigIndex.name: t1e1ConfigIndex
t1e1ConfigIndex.description: This object is the index into the t1e1Table.

t1e1Description.name: t1e1Description
t1e1Description.description: Contains a textual description of the port.

t1e1Mode.name: t1e1Mode
t1e1Mode.description: This object identifies the port as either a Network (long-haul) or DTE (short-haul) port.

t1e1FrameType.name: t1e1FrameType
t1e1FrameType.description: Selects the framing for the network side of the DSU/CSU.

t1e1LineCode.name: t1e1LineCode
t1e1LineCode.description: Selects the network side line coding.

t1e1LineBuildOut.name: t1e1LineBuildOut
t1e1LineBuildOut.description: Selects the line build out for the network interface. The options are: t1e1LineBuildOut0db indicates a line build out of 0db t1e1LineBuildOut75db indicates a line build out of -7.5db t1e1LineBuildOut15db indicates a line build out of -15db t1e1LineBuildOut225db indicates a line build out of -22.5db

t1e1Timing.name: t1e1Timing
t1e1Timing.description: Sets the timing source to synchronize the unit's internal timing generators.

t1e1StationInTiming.name: t1e1StationInTiming
t1e1StationInTiming.description: Selects the input timing if t1e1Timing is set to Station.

t1e1StationTiming.name: t1e1StationTiming
t1e1StationTiming.description: Selects the N-multiple when Station Input Timing is set to either NX56 or NX65. The N range is 1..24

t1e1PRM.name: t1e1PRM
t1e1PRM.description: Enables the ANSI T1.403 Performance Report Message functions.

t1e1ZeroSuppress.name: t1e1ZeroSuppress
t1e1ZeroSuppress.description: Determines whether ones density insertion is activated after 15 zeros . To ensure compliance with TR54016, this field must be enabled.

t1e1NationalBit.name: t1e1NationalBit
t1e1NationalBit.description: Selects a national bit to create a 4-kbps datalink between the endpoint units.

t1e1KeepAlive.name: t1e1KeepAlive
t1e1KeepAlive.description: Selects keep alive framed and unframed ones when the unit detects LOS or OOF.

t1e1CRC4Mode.name: t1e1CRC4Mode
t1e1CRC4Mode.description: Selects whether CRC4 is enabled or disabled.

t1e1DSXLevel.name: t1e1DSXLevel
t1e1DSXLevel.description: Selects the DSX1 interface output level.

t1e1CRC.name: t1e1CRC
t1e1CRC.description: Determines whether received CRC data is passed through or regenerated.

t1e1FDLPassThrough.name: t1e1FDLPassThrough
t1e1FDLPassThrough.description: Determines whether the ESF FDL passes through the CSU or terminates.

t1e1AudibleAlarm.name: t1e1AudibleAlarm
t1e1AudibleAlarm.description: If applicable, Enables or Disables the CSU's internal buzzer which alerts users of an alarm condition.

t1e1Function.name: t1e1Function
t1e1Function.description: Specifies the function the network port will perform in the unit. The options are: t1e1FunctionNetwork (Independent network port) t1e1FunctionSlaved (Slaved to another network port) t1e1FunctionBackup (Automatic Protection Switching Backup for another network port)

t1e1AlarmTable.name: t1e1AlarmTable
t1e1AlarmTable.description: The T1 and E1 Alarm Table.

t1e1AlarmIndex.name: t1e1AlarmIndex
t1e1AlarmIndex.description: This object is the index into the t1e1Table.

t1e1StatusSummary.name: t1e1StatusSummary
t1e1StatusSummary.description: This object provides a summary of the port status.

t1e1AlarmSummary.name: t1e1AlarmSummary
t1e1AlarmSummary.description: This object provides a summary of the port alarms.

t1e1ESStatus.name: t1e1ESStatus
t1e1ESStatus.description: Reports if an Errored Second condition exists.

t1e1ESCount.name: t1e1ESCount
t1e1ESCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds an Errored Second condition has existed.

t1e1ESThreshold.name: t1e1ESThreshold
t1e1ESThreshold.description: Sets the Errored Seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1ESAlarm.name: t1e1ESAlarm
t1e1ESAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Errors Seconds threshold is exceeded.

t1e1SESStatus.name: t1e1SESStatus
t1e1SESStatus.description: Reports if a Severely Errored condition exists.

t1e1SESCount.name: t1e1SESCount
t1e1SESCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds a Severely Errored condition has existed.

t1e1SESThreshold.name: t1e1SESThreshold
t1e1SESThreshold.description: Sets the Severely Errored seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1SESAlarm.name: t1e1SESAlarm
t1e1SESAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Severely Errors Seconds threshold is exceeded.

t1e1LOSSStatus.name: t1e1LOSSStatus
t1e1LOSSStatus.description: Reports if a Loss of Signal condition exists.

t1e1LOSSCount.name: t1e1LOSSCount
t1e1LOSSCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds a Loss of Signal condition has existed.

t1e1LOSSThreshold.name: t1e1LOSSThreshold
t1e1LOSSThreshold.description: Sets the Loss of Signal seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1LOSSAlarm.name: t1e1LOSSAlarm
t1e1LOSSAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Loss of Signal Seconds threshold is exceeded.

t1e1UASStatus.name: t1e1UASStatus
t1e1UASStatus.description: Reports if an Unavailable condition exists.

t1e1UASCount.name: t1e1UASCount
t1e1UASCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds an Unavailable condition has existed.

t1e1UASThreshold.name: t1e1UASThreshold
t1e1UASThreshold.description: Sets the unavailable seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1UASAlarm.name: t1e1UASAlarm
t1e1UASAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Unavailable Seconds threshold is exceeded.

t1e1CSSStatus.name: t1e1CSSStatus
t1e1CSSStatus.description: Reports if a Controlled Slip condition exists.

t1e1CSSCount.name: t1e1CSSCount
t1e1CSSCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds in which at least one Controlled Slip occurred.

t1e1CSSThreshold.name: t1e1CSSThreshold
t1e1CSSThreshold.description: Sets the Controlled Slip seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1CSSAlarm.name: t1e1CSSAlarm
t1e1CSSAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Controlled Slip seconds threshold is exceeded.

t1e1BPVSStatus.name: t1e1BPVSStatus
t1e1BPVSStatus.description: Reports if a Bipolar Violation Error condition exists.

t1e1BPVSCount.name: t1e1BPVSCount
t1e1BPVSCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds a Bipolar Violation Error condition has existed.

t1e1BPVSThreshold.name: t1e1BPVSThreshold
t1e1BPVSThreshold.description: Sets the Bipolar Violation Error seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1BPVSAlarm.name: t1e1BPVSAlarm
t1e1BPVSAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Bipolar Violation Error seconds threshold is exceeded.

t1e1OOFSStatus.name: t1e1OOFSStatus
t1e1OOFSStatus.description: Indicates that the unit is unable to synchronize on the incoming framing pattern.

t1e1OOFSCount.name: t1e1OOFSCount
t1e1OOFSCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds an OOF condition has existed.

t1e1OOFSThreshold.name: t1e1OOFSThreshold
t1e1OOFSThreshold.description: Sets the OOF seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1OOFSAlarm.name: t1e1OOFSAlarm
t1e1OOFSAlarm.description: Indicates if an OOF seconds alarm condition exists.

t1e1AISStatus.name: t1e1AISStatus
t1e1AISStatus.description: Indicates that the unit is receiving an unframed all ones pattern.

t1e1AISCount.name: t1e1AISCount
t1e1AISCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds an Unframed All Ones condition has existed.

t1e1AISThreshold.name: t1e1AISThreshold
t1e1AISThreshold.description: Sets the AIS seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1AISAlarm.name: t1e1AISAlarm
t1e1AISAlarm.description: Indicates if an Unframed All Ones alarm condition exists.

t1e1RASStatus.name: t1e1RASStatus
t1e1RASStatus.description: Reports if a Remote (Yellow) Alarm condition exists.

t1e1RASCount.name: t1e1RASCount
t1e1RASCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds a Remote (Yellow) Alarm condition has existed.

t1e1RASThreshold.name: t1e1RASThreshold
t1e1RASThreshold.description: Sets the RAS seconds alarm threshold. Setting this field to 0 disables the alarm. The threshold can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1RASAlarm.name: t1e1RASAlarm
t1e1RASAlarm.description: This status indicates if a Remote (Yellow) Alarm exists.

t1e1AlarmResetTimer.name: t1e1AlarmResetTimer
t1e1AlarmResetTimer.description: Sets the Alarm Reset Timer, this field can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

t1e1AlarmReset.name: t1e1AlarmReset
t1e1AlarmReset.description: This is used to clear the current alarm counts.

ddsNetConfigTable.name: ddsNetConfigTable
ddsNetConfigTable.description: The dds Network Interface Configuration Table.

ddsNetConfigTableEntry.name: ddsNetConfigTableEntry
ddsNetConfigTableEntry.description: An entry in the Network Interface Table.

ddsNetDescription.name: ddsNetDescription
ddsNetDescription.description: Contains a textual description of the port.

ddsNetRate.name: ddsNetRate
ddsNetRate.description: This object is the identifier of the current DDS network rate. The values mean: ddsNetRate2400 the DDS network interface is operating at 2400bps ddsNetRate4800 the DDS network interface is operating at 4800bps ddsNetRate9600 the DDS network interface is operating at 9600bps ddsNetRate19200 the DDS network interface is operating at 19200bps ddsNetRate38400 the DDS network interface is operating at 38400bps ddsNetRate56000 the DDS network interface is operating at 56000bps ddsNetRate64000 the DDS network interface is operating at 64000bps

ddsNetMode.name: ddsNetMode
ddsNetMode.description: This variable describes mode in which data is being sent from the DDS unit back towards the network. Changing the value of this variable can cause a loss of remote communications. The values mean: ddsNetModeNormal (DDS-I) normal data mode of operation ddsNetModeProprietaryTXPI (DDS-I) data being sent out on the DDS network is in a proprietary mode to allow for remote communications, rate adaption, and SYNC to ASYNC modes ddsNetMode64KClearChannel (DDS-II) A special case of DDS-II, where the line rate is 72K, the data rate is 64K, and there is no secondary channel. ddsNetMode64KCCProprietaryTXPII (DDS-II) A special case of DDS-II, where the line rate is 72K, the data rate is 64K, and there is no secondary channel. In addition, the data being sent out on the DDS network is in a proprietary mode to allow for remote communications, rate adaption, SYNC to ASYNC, and/or TDM modes.

ddsNetTimingSource.name: ddsNetTimingSource
ddsNetTimingSource.description: This variable describes the current timing source for the DDS network interface. The values mean: ddsNetTimingNet unit dependant upon network for DDS network interface timing ddsNetTimingInt unit supplying timing for DDS network interface ddsNetTimingDTE unit dependant upon DTE device for network interface timing ddsNetTimingPort1 unit dependant upon serial port 1 device for network interface timing ddsNetTimingPort2 unit dependant upon serial port 2 device for network interface timing

ddsNetRemComm.name: ddsNetRemComm
ddsNetRemComm.description: This variable describes the current setting for the remote communications link. The values mean: ddsNetRemCommEnabled remote communications can be carried out end to end ddsNetRemCommDisabled remote communications are not allowed ddsNetRemCommNotAvailable this unit does not support remote communications

ddsNetCircuitAssur.name: ddsNetCircuitAssur
ddsNetCircuitAssur.description: This variable describes the current setting for the circuit assurance option. The values mean: ddsNetCircuitAssurEnabled Circuit Assurance is enabled and the integrity of the DDS loop will be maintained ddsNetCircuitAssurDisabled Circuit Assurance is disabled ddsNetCircuitAssurNotAvailable this unit does not support Circuit Assurance

ddsNetAntiStrTimer.name: ddsNetAntiStrTimer
ddsNetAntiStrTimer.description: This variable describes the current setting for the anti streaming timer. The values mean: ddsNetAntiStrTimerOff the AntiStreaming Timer is off ddsNetAntiStrTimer10 the AntiStreaming Timer is set to 10 seconds ddsNetAntiStrTimer30 the AntiStreaming Timer is set to 30 seconds ddsNetAntiStrTimer60 the AntiStreaming Timer is set to 60 seconds

ddsNetAlarmTable.name: ddsNetAlarmTable
ddsNetAlarmTable.description: The dds Network Interface Alarm Table.

ddsNetStatusSummary.name: ddsNetStatusSummary
ddsNetStatusSummary.description: This object provides a summary of the port status.

ddsNetAlarmSummary.name: ddsNetAlarmSummary
ddsNetAlarmSummary.description: This object provides a summary of the port alarms.

ddsNetLOSStatus.name: ddsNetLOSStatus
ddsNetLOSStatus.description: Reports if a Loss of Signal condition exists.

ddsNetLOSCount.name: ddsNetLOSCount
ddsNetLOSCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds the unit received signal has been interrupted.

ddsNetLOSThreshold.name: ddsNetLOSThreshold
ddsNetLOSThreshold.description: A period, measured in seconds, in which the DDS received signal is interrupted.

ddsNetLOSAlarm.name: ddsNetLOSAlarm
ddsNetLOSAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Loss of Signal Seconds threshold is exceeded.

ddsNetOOFStatus.name: ddsNetOOFStatus
ddsNetOOFStatus.description: Reports if an Out of Frame condition exists.

ddsNetOOFCount.name: ddsNetOOFCount
ddsNetOOFCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds the unit has received the out of frame code.

ddsNetOOFThreshold.name: ddsNetOOFThreshold
ddsNetOOFThreshold.description: A period, measured in seconds, in which the Out Of Frame code is received or a frame sync loss occurred.

ddsNetOOFAlarm.name: ddsNetOOFAlarm
ddsNetOOFAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Out of Frame Seconds threshold is exceeded.

ddsNetOOSStatus.name: ddsNetOOSStatus
ddsNetOOSStatus.description: Reports if Out of Service codes are received.

ddsNetOOSCount.name: ddsNetOOSCount
ddsNetOOSCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds the unit has received the out of service code.

ddsNetOOSThreshold.name: ddsNetOOSThreshold
ddsNetOOSThreshold.description: A period, measured in seconds, in which the Out Of Service code is received.

ddsNetOOSAlarm.name: ddsNetOOSAlarm
ddsNetOOSAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Out of Service Seconds threshold is exceeded.

ddsNetFDLStatus.name: ddsNetFDLStatus
ddsNetFDLStatus.description: Reports if Facility Data Link errors have occurred.

ddsNetFDLCount.name: ddsNetFDLCount
ddsNetFDLCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds in which FDL errors have occurred.

ddsNetFDLThreshold.name: ddsNetFDLThreshold
ddsNetFDLThreshold.description: A period, measured in seconds, in which FDL errors have occurred.

ddsNetFDLAlarm.name: ddsNetFDLAlarm
ddsNetFDLAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Facility Data Link threshold is exceeded.

ddsNetAlarmResetTimer.name: ddsNetAlarmResetTimer
ddsNetAlarmResetTimer.description: Sets the Alarm Reset Timer, this field can be set to any value in the range 0 to 900.

ddsNetAlarmReset.name: ddsNetAlarmReset
ddsNetAlarmReset.description: This is used to clear the current alarm counts.

ddsNetBPVStatus.name: ddsNetBPVStatus
ddsNetBPVStatus.description: Reports if a Bipolar violation event occurred in the last second.

ddsNetBPVCount.name: ddsNetBPVCount
ddsNetBPVCount.description: This count contains the number of consecutive seconds the unit received bipolar violations.

ddsNetBPVThreshold.name: ddsNetBPVThreshold
ddsNetBPVThreshold.description: A period, measured in seconds, in which the unit receives bipolar violations before an alarm is triggered.

ddsNetBPVAlarm.name: ddsNetBPVAlarm
ddsNetBPVAlarm.description: This status indicates if the Bipolar violation Seconds threshold is exceeded.

serialDteConfigTableEntry.name: serialDteConfigTableEntry
serialDteConfigTableEntry.description: An entry in the serial DTE Config Table.

serialDteDescription.name: serialDteDescription
serialDteDescription.description: Contains a textual description of the port.

serialDteType.name: serialDteType
serialDteType.description: Selects the DTE port type if applicable.

serialDteInvertData.name: serialDteInvertData

netAPSConfigTable.description: One to One network Automatic Protection Switching (APS) configuration parameters table.

netAPSConfigOtherifIndex.name: netAPSConfigOtherifIndex
netAPSConfigOtherifIndex.description: MIB-II ifIndex of the other interface involved with the APS.

netAPSConfigMode.name: netAPSConfigMode
netAPSConfigMode.description: tr54017 - Implements TR54017 autoABswitch - Implements a single ended A/B switch between two independent lines masterAltCarrier - Master side of alternate carrier APS slaveAltCarrier - Slave side of alternate carrier APS

netAPSConfigRevert.name: netAPSConfigRevert
netAPSConfigRevert.description: disabled - Service does not return to the primary line until the backup line fails. enabled - Service automatically returns to the primary line when the primary line is able to carry service again.

netAPSConfigManualInhibit.name: netAPSConfigManualInhibit
netAPSConfigManualInhibit.description: Disabled - Neither line is manually inhibited from carrying service. ThisLine - This line is manually inhibited from carrying service. OtherLine - The other line is manually inhibited from carrying service.

netAPSConfigAvailabilityTimer.name: netAPSConfigAvailabilityTimer
netAPSConfigAvailabilityTimer.description: The line availability timer represents the minimum amount of time that is free of errors in active events that must expire before this line is returned to service availability. The timer is in seconds ranging from 0 - 900 seconds.

netAPSConfigESThreshold.name: netAPSConfigESThreshold
netAPSConfigESThreshold.description: This parameter is the number of erred seconds in a 15-minute period needed before a transfer request is triggered. A setting of zero disables this trigger.

netAPSConfigESCount.name: netAPSConfigESCount
netAPSConfigESCount.description: This parameter is the number of erred seconds in the current 15-minute interval. This count is reset at the beginning of a new 15-minute interval.

netAPSConfigESSwitchEvent.name: netAPSConfigESSwitchEvent
netAPSConfigESSwitchEvent.description: This status indicates if exceeding the ES threshold caused a transfer to the other line.

netAPSConfigCSESThreshold.name: netAPSConfigCSESThreshold
netAPSConfigCSESThreshold.description: This parameter is the number of consecutive SES needed before a transfer request is triggered. A setting of zero disables this trigger.

netAPSConfigCSESCount.name: netAPSConfigCSESCount
netAPSConfigCSESCount.description: This parameter is the number of consecutive SES detected. This count stops when 900 is reached and is reset when a non-SES is detected.

netAPSConfigCSESSwitchEvent.name: netAPSConfigCSESSwitchEvent
netAPSConfigCSESSwitchEvent.description: This status indicates if exceeding the consecutive SES threshold caused a transfer to the other line.

netAPSConfigStatusBitmap.name: netAPSConfigStatusBitmap
netAPSConfigStatusBitmap.description: TR54017 defined bitmap status for this line interface: Value is 1 if this line is carrying service. Value is 2 if this line is in a failed state. Value is 4 if this line is in an inhibit state. Value is 8 if this line is looped back. Value is 16 if the other line is in a failed state. Value is 32 if the other line is in an inhibit state. Value is 64 if the other line is looped back. Value is 128 if the manual inhibit is active Note that multiple status conditions may exist at the same time. The failed state is determined when carrier fails, or the ES threshold is reached, or the consecutive SES threshold is reached. The inhibit state is set when the manual inhibit setting affects this line or the line is inhibited by the remote end.
